deck_excerpt: Freki (Red TRANSCENDER) - Yggdrasil 5F  lv : 15 star   Yugioh 5ds duel transer
Geri (Blue TRANSCENDER) - Yggdrasil 5F  lv : 15 star  Yugioh 5ds duel transer

deck_description:
The deck is just a pure Marincess list for a small price which doesn't use any staples (yet) so it's a decent way to get started and learn Link Summoning since that is the only thing this deck does

The fun part about Marincess is that they really like the style of hand traps as actual traps and Marincess Wave is basically one of the strongest trap cards that this game has (so it's a good thing it only really shines in Marincess) with an effect that Infinite Impermanence wishes it could have.

The main strategy is usually to get a large Link monster into your EMZ and turn it into a Towers with either Battle Ocean, Wave or Snow.

Otherwise the deck can be cheeky with Zealantis since you can lock yourself to only be able to Special Summon WATER monsters with Dive or Coral Anemone. The fun fact about Zealantis effect: You Special Summon all the monsters back that both players control so if you get WATER locked, your Zealantis keeps every non-Water monster banished since you are not allowed to summon them back to your opponent's field turning him into a pretty potent board wipe against non-WATER decks.

Keep in mind that this list is mostly a starting point into the game where you can cheese some wins in a format that doesn't run staple hand traps so a lot of the traps can be taken out for non-engine like Ash, Veiler, Nibiru, Impermanence and all that stuff instead

deck_excerpt: Unleashing the Power of the Ra-Horus Deck: Ultimate Strategy Guide
deck_description:
The Ra-Horus deck combines the powerful synergy between the "Horus the Black Flame Dragon" series and "The Winged Dragon of Ra" to create a formidable strategy that controls the field while setting up massive attacks. The core idea is to summon Horus to gain immunity from spell cards and to set up powerful tribute plays to summon Ra with overwhelming attack power. Key cards include Horus the Black Flame Dragon LV6 and LV8, which protect against spells, and The Winged Dragon of Ra, whose ATK can be maximized using Ancient Chant or Soul Crossing for a swift victory.

The deck also features consistency cards like Maxx "C" for draw power, Fist of Fate for monster negation, and Sphere Mode to clear threats. Spell cards like Millennium Revelation and Monster Reborn help recycle powerful cards, enabling efficient resource management. The strategy often involves controlling the opponent's moves using cards like Canopic Protector and building towards an OTK with Ra boosted by Blaze Cannon.

Complicated strategy: A complex strategy involves baiting your opponent into summoning strong monsters, then using Soul Crossing to tribute them for Ra’s powerful summon. This allows you to disrupt your opponent while setting up Ra with Ancient Chant, boosting its ATK to levels that can one-shot an opponent. If necessary, use Horus LV8 to secure the field from spell card threats and gradually take control of the game, preparing for Ra’s arrival.

 

El deck de Ra-Horus combina la poderosa sinergia entre la serie de "Horus el Dragón de Llama Negra" y "El Dragón Alado de Ra" para crear una estrategia formidable que controla el campo mientras prepara ataques masivos. La idea principal es invocar a Horus para obtener inmunidad a cartas mágicas y preparar jugadas de tributo potentes para invocar a Ra con un poder de ataque abrumador. Las cartas clave incluyen Horus el Dragón de Llama Negra LV6 y LV8, que protegen contra cartas mágicas, y El Dragón Alado de Ra, cuyo ATK se puede maximizar usando Canto Ancestral o Cruzando Almas para una victoria rápida.

El mazo también cuenta con cartas de consistencia como Maxx "C" para robar cartas, Puño del Destino para la negación de monstruos y Modo Esfera para eliminar amenazas. Cartas mágicas como Revelación del Milenio y Renace el Monstruo ayudan a reciclar cartas poderosas, permitiendo una gestión eficiente de recursos. La estrategia implica controlar los movimientos del oponente con cartas como Protector Canópico y preparar un OTK con Ra mejorado por Cañón de Llamas.

Estrategia complicada: Una estrategia compleja implica provocar que tu oponente invoque monstruos fuertes, luego usar Cruzando Almas para tributarlos e invocar a Ra de forma poderosa. Esto permite interrumpir a tu oponente mientras preparas a Ra con Canto Ancestral, aumentando su ATK a niveles que pueden acabar con un oponente de un solo golpe. Si es necesario, usa Horus LV8 para asegurar el campo de amenazas de cartas mágicas y tomar control gradual del juego, preparando la llegada de Ra.

Agent of Creation Control

This deck leverages the powerful effects of the "Agent of Creation" cards to control the field and disrupt your opponent's plays. Key strategies include:

  • Resource Control: Use cards like "Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring" and "Infinite Impermanence" to negate your opponent's activations and limit their resources.
  • Board Domination: Summon high-powered monsters like "Master Hyperion" and "Majesty Hyperion" to control the board and deal massive damage.
  • Card Advantage: Utilize cards like "Pot of Desires" and "The Sacred Waters in the Sky" to draw extra cards and gain an advantage.
  • Recovery and Recursion: Employ cards like "Monster Reborn" and "Called by the Grave" to bring back key monsters from the graveyard.
  • Extra Deck Power Plays: Summon powerful Extra Deck monsters like "Celestial Knightlord Parshath" and "Accesscode Talker" to swing the game in your favor.

This deck excels at controlling the pace of the game and overwhelming opponents with powerful plays. With a strong focus on disruption and resource management, it's a versatile deck that can adapt to various strategies.

deck_excerpt: Unchained + Dark Hole Dragon + D/D/D engine
deck_description:
Kind of cookie cutter as far as Unchained decks without Yubel (or non-engine) go. The deck is still pretty strong all things considered HOWEVER since this is a budget variant and I prefer to deck build without non-engine it won't be all that competitive due to instalosing against any established boards that offer up to 2 negates depending on the quality of your starting hand.

The deck (if uninterrupted) can pull off some nutty plays for a few interruptions though and if you have the money (or the card in your collection), then S:P Little Knight will feel right at home in some more optimised variants of the list.

As for non-engine, the Dark Hole Dragon (and the Dark Holes) can easily be replaced and a few Unchained monsters can also be cut to 1 for a more competitive future approach where you actually get to interact with your opponent turn 1. Wailing is another easy to cut spot and the D/D engine can also be cut down a peg if you wish to add a few cards from the Yubel package for an even higher ceiling (but also a higher price...) though if Sharvara ever comes back to more copies we of course will max out on him.

For the main strategy you will usually attempt to combo off to at least end on High King Caesar and/or Unchained Soul of Rage along with at least 1 Unchained Trap set. Rage can then Link off into Knightmare Unicorn (or Little Knight if you have it) for a fun double interruption. And from your second turn on you are off to the races for something bigger.

deck_description:
Category: Tournament Meta Decks (TCG)

Tournament Meta Decks are current-level Meta Decks that are capable of going up against the best of the best. These are curated lists that cannot be uploaded by regular users.

Creator: Andrew Powelson

Tournament: Houston WCQ Regional – November 2nd 2024

Placement: Top 8

My deck looks so much different, but that's great, in the first deck I didn't have access to very many good monsters, I only got 1 copy of my strongest fiend monster from that deck which SUCKS, and what's worse is I basically only had 1 effect monster, being reaper of the cards, which is great for trap removal but it costs a tribute.  So with this new deck I added the new tribute fiend monster to trick people into thinking it was a reaper of the cards instead, I also got some better spell and trap support and even got 1 fusion monster, my rule on fusions is if the fusion monster itself is a fiend I'm allowed to have both materials in my deck needed for the summon, if both materials for the fusion summon are fiends I can have the fusion monster.  Some bad news now, last deck I didn't have enough fiends to fill up my deck so I filled it with walls and even a 2 tribute secret rare in the form of Tri-Horned dragon, it won me a duel in the series I'm doing with my deck but with this new pack adding so many fiends I had to take them out.  At least my new boss monster Skull knight can have its materials searched by sangan and can be boosted by my Yami field spell.  Also for clarification about the extra dark energy card and why I didn't have it in my first deck, during each new pack I'm allowed to grab one common from the previous pack I did, one rare or one common from 2 packs ago, one super rare, rare, or common from 3 packs ago, one Secret rare, Super rare, Rare, Or common from 4 packs ago, and 1 card of any rarity from every other pack before that.

Welcome! In this deck, the aim is to seal the victory with alternate win-condition card called "Number 88: Gimmick Puppet of Leo". So, hear my roar!

 

 

Gameplan

1) Bring forth Tethys by replacing Capricious/Aces/Corobane and draw your whole deck...

  • Whenever you draw a Fairy, reveal it to draw another card with Tethys. You can keep it going until you can't draw anymore.
  • If you hit non-Fairy, you stop movement. So, continue with Ixchel and alike to trigger Tethys again. Note that "Extra-Foolish Burial" can also let you draw by sending Garura to GY, as long as you don't Set any Spell/Trap by accident.
  • Know that card draw has to be caused by an effect, not as cost, in order to draw a card with Tethys. For example, using "Upstart Goblin", seen in Side Deck, won't do any help for Tethys but "Into the Void" will. Remember this rule well.

2) Special Summon Valkyria and Link Summon Reprodocus with Tethys + Valkyria. Then, place "Light Barrier" and Lebellman + Eccentrick into Pendulum Zones.

3) Pendulum Summon 2 x Level 5 + Carbon + 1 x Level 4 + Any. There, XYZ Summon Knight with Carbon and Level 4 monster as materials. You have to detach Carbon from Knight to Special Summon The World or you will lose the game due to deck-out, which you will see why later on.

4) When you have Special Summoned The World, choose the outcome as heads to skip your opponent's turn at the cost of sending two monsters you control to GY. Then, activate Lebellman to change Level 5 monsters you have into Level 6.

5) XYZ Summon Number 25 with 2 x Level 6 monsters as materials, right behind Reprodocus and change the Attribute of Number 25 to DARK with Reprodocus. You can replace Number 25 with Number 88 by playing Astral Force.

6) To win with Number 88, we need to detach 3 materials from Number 88 while placing 3 x Destiny Counters on itself. However, we need to clear our backrow. Fortunately, Eccentrick can pop Lebellman and we can start using Number 88.

7) End your turn and use The World to send two monsters you control to GY, one of which has to be Fairy monster. Had you not sent Carbon to GY in #3, you wouldn't have been able to shuffle Carbon into Main Deck but you can.

8) When it's your turn, activate Astral Force from your GY to not draw anything. Detach a card from Number 88 and end your turn with The World. Just keep Number 88 present, you will be fine.

9) When it's your move, detach last material of Number 88 to win the game!

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Chicken Game" can be either found within "The Most Dangerous Race of the Cosmos!" Secret Pack or "Tricky Reception" Timed Pack to save 90 UR!

- "Into The Void" can be found either within "The Infinite Void" or "Life Force Control System" Secret Packs to save 90 SR!

- "Darklord Ixchel" can be found either within "The Opening Act of an Apocalypse" or "Deceitful Wings of Darkness" Secret Packs to save 90 SR!

- "Trickstar Corobane" can be found within "Essence of Flora and Ocean" Secret Pack to save 90 SR!

- "Chaos Valkyria" can be found within "Inevitability of Chaos" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "World Soul - Carbon" can be either found within "The Ones Who Serve Ra" or "Hope Sprouting in the Spring Breeze" Secret Packs to save 30 SR!

- "Arcana Force XXI - The World" + "Light Barrier" can be found within "Hand of Fate" Secret Pack to save 30 SR and 30 UR!

- "Rank-Up-Magic Astral Force" can be found within "Number Recall" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Number 88: Gimmick Puppet of Leo" can be found within "Colossal Mech" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 390 SR and 150 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. If you have any questions, feel free to ask. Have fun in Master Duel!

deck_excerpt: Me in a yuri competition when the XYZ archetype walks in
deck_description: Me in a yuri competition when the XYZ archetype walks in

Its been so long since I last posted any deck, the generic boss hits really made a lot of my fav decks much weaker :C

that aside im super happy insects got support in ROTA another very good engine since ragnaraika. dang the ragnaraika starters are expensive now, lifes rough when youre a student again 

that aside lets start with the deck build options:

Deck Over view

This deck focuses on more hand traps as another form of interuption, the battlewasp engine itself is pretty much powerful enough to start plays so additional free bodies and externders like Guard Mantis, praying mantis etc were used over more starters

Krawler Soma package:  still a very good option to provide field value for link climbing as an alternative starter, but I did not include it in this build as the 2x lv2 garnets can be quite annoying in a 40-45 card deck. This package is more for 60 card variants imo. Sure the krawler package would make the huge endboard easier but the risk of bricking is also higher.

Scout Buggies: another decent starter/ extender, 2-3 copies could work, but ultimately they to be normal summoned or otherwise done in more gimmicky ways like Atlas effect or Saturnas revive. Used to be a nice starter but imo its a bit lacking now compared to battlewasp. The normal summon is usually dedicated to the battlewasps. There are other ways to make Cicada king (which will be mentioned below).

 

Starters: Bascially you want to open with the new Battlewasp Lv5 (Rapier) + 1 extra insect in your hand or ways to access it. Given the density of insect monsters in the deck this chance is high enough to be considered consistent. You can use the battlwasp lv2 (Sting) to search it, Resonance insect can search and Armed Rebeelion can make sure Resonance insect does its job. From there onwards you just combo off into the huge insect board. There will be situations when you only get to Rapier after some combos so by that time youd want to consider if you want to go through the full battlewasp line to attempt making grand partisan or just settle with what you have. 

Extenders: The deck has ample extenders that can ss themselves when insects are around but even with that, youll find situations of bad luck when you brick without enough stuff to link climb. Guard Mantis, 2x Twin bow and Beetrooper Descend are completely free bodies hopefully to reduce the brickyness as they can all add bodies to the field for free. 

if your combo goes will youll need 2 discards, one from Rapier and one from Pickofalena, maybe more when fusion summoning. For that sake, Goki pole, Praying mantis and Beargram were chosen, these are excellent discard targets or send-to-gy targets for Resonance insects. Goki-pole allows you to search any lv4 insect which can be extenders (Roller, Guard mantis), Normal summon targets (Resonance, "C"), or further discard fooder (praying mantis). Praying mantis can generate a token by banishing itself from the gy and beargram is main deck powerhouse as well as resonance insect banisher

The one copy of Retaliating "C" is played as an extra normal summon target or equip from the our link 2s and can search Resonance insect or Supply Soldier.

Note that supply soldier is not easy to search, only resonance insect and "C" can search it, so plan your searches, as these 2 might also need to fetch you other useful stuff. 

Endboard: Your goal is to set a Ragnaraika Trap (Hunting Dance) + Heavy Cavalry of the Indestructible Insects + Grand Partisan on the field, but usually, you can do far more than that with an additional stag sovereign + followup + maybe Saturnas to plus off your quick effect banishes

Hidden effects (?):

1. Scale bomber and Sting the Poison are interrupts while on the field. Scale bomber can tribute itself, Sting cannot

2. Arbalest has an effect when destroyed by the opponent which allows you to ss a battlewasp from hand or gy

*3. The Ragnaraika links can send ed monsters back to the ed to ss themselves from the gy but if its like the beetrooper link 2 that banishes itself or if its a token the ss wont work and you lose field value.

(*3 This needs to be confirmed as in ocg simulators returning stuff to the ed does not work)

Banishers: The deck needs some banishers to tigger Resonance insect and Grand Partisan. After a lot of testing 2x Resoance insects is usually enough to cycle in 1 turn. Ive decided to take Beargram and Roller as my banish 3 and banish 1 main deck monsters. Beargram's gy ss and boardwipe is also very powerful. I honestly dont think Doom Dozer is any good as an extender because Roller does the same job for less, sure Doom Dozer hits harder but insects have big bodies anyways.

Beetrooper Spell Traps and Hercules: Since both Satrunas and Stinglancer can search beetrooper spell traps, theres a lot of flexibility in options.

If you have enough resources, search the trap as interuption. If you need extenders, search Descend, if you have either in your hand, search for the other 2. If you need a banish to trigger Saturnas, search Roller (which is also an extender). If you need to recycle some banished stuff or want an extra beat stick, search Hercules.

Honestly, Hercules is quite the brick, but its recycle-banished insect ability is really good.

Ragnaraika Traps: Most builds ive seen just carry the Hunting Dance as an extra pop, but Woe is surprisingly good for grind games and resource recycling, only downside is it is a plant monster when summoned. 

Cicada King: Instead of using 2x lv3 monsters, this can be done during the battlewasp combo, but is more an icing on the cake. The deck can pushout enough interuption now so Cicada king isnt too necessary unless your build speciallizes in scary moth lock. 

SO, 1. do not use Pin's effect to burn.

2. After Sachi's effect to normal summon, activate Battlewasp wind, and normal Albarest

3. Albarest effect to revive Pin and  Battlewasp wind, search Twin bow and ss it

4. Banish Rapier to lower Albarest lv by 1 so you can xyz cicada king

5. Use Pin's Burn effect and Cicada king detach Albarest to negate pin

6. Cicada king's effect to change itself's battle position and revive Albarest so you can still make Grand Partisan

Extra Deck:

The only good insect cards are all there. a 2nd copy of Heavy Cavalry , Picofalena could be useful.

the Traptrix link 3 can be an decent beater and negate/pop given this deck runs 3x imperm and the searchable Hunting Dance

Shinobi insect is a wierd one honestly, its mainly used to convert non-insect monsters into link value, but the card itself doesnt do anything good. Its mainly used if your oppenet drops nib/kaijus or the likes on you or if you used TT-Talent to steal your opponents monster

 

Overall im really happy with the insect support, its definitely much stronger now and fair rogue option imo. Though it still dies to nib and gets hurt greatly by boardwipes, given the deck doesnt have any s/t resistance. The presence of Heavy Cavalry and Grand Partisan helps to  reduce the damage from your opponents boardwipes but its still not enough with just the 2 imo.

Insects could definitely benefit from a good link 1 or another good link 2 that uses more generic materials. Its solid engine with a decent endboard, but could still use better endboard pieces and links.

deck_name: skull servant ft lightsworn fiendsmith horus tear
deck_description:
This deck has been once of the most fun i have played in months, it was october i wanted to play zombie, the meta feel stale. This started as an OTK skull servant deck, but with tenpai around why even true. So this was created with a few ideas for some youtuber.

i dont play often due to work but top my locals twice, out of the three times i played.

the synegy is hilarious, as nobody knows where to hit with handtraps, the boards you make after nib are just damn right illegal.

the basic play is to mill the deck using the wight card, they trigger the lightsworn to mill more, the new lightsworn weiss is a light fiend, free desirae or fiendsmith sequence for kaleido-heart which just so happens to be a fiend fusion.

The skull servant also give you free extender in king of skull servant from deck and grave with wightlord, mezuki, prince and wightmare.

The horus field card fixes hand by shuffling back into deck, and mills 4 with zombie vampire, which could also be made with the lightsworn synchro and punishment dragon. There are only 2 imsety, because i wanted to reduce the number of once per turn effect.

this deck is greedy and complex, sometime feeling like solitaire if the opponant doesnt draw any handtrap but man is it fun.

there is space to play with in term of non-engine, the trap package can be swapped for a shaddoll package for winda locking.

i leave the side deck for you guys to play with....
this deck is off of the endymion cards and some other engines to make spell counters

deck_excerpt: Madolche Meta deck, trying to be competive and rogue tier
deck_description:
Hi guys, I'm kinda new to Yugi oh and i tried to build a Madolche deck which could fight against most meta deck.

DECKLIST:

DECK:

MADOLCHE CARDS:

we have x3 of the classic madolche starters: magileine

                                                                                                    Pettingsoeur

                                                                                                     Anjelly

we have 1 puddingcess since we don't want it in the hand,

 2 messengelato and 2 hootcake who are necessary to tuto our spell (you could also have 2 and 1 but i prefer having 2 hootcake in case i have 1 in hand since we usally spe him from the deck and it could block us)

 for the spell;1 ticket, 1 salon and 1 chateau: we don't need more beacause messengelato can tuto each of them 

 for the trap; 1 dessert and 1 promenade. they are both the only 2 good trap for madolche but not necessary to play the deck (we prefer having infinite impermanence instead for exemple) so we can play with 1 of them only

VERNUSYLPH:

For the engine we stick with Vernusylph cards, the usual for Madolche. i go with the minimum to optimized the number of handtrap while having the deck being able to play correctly:

 

Duckling x3 because is the best, we can spe any earth monster in hand or gy with him if we have it in hand so it's perfect for us. + we can add in any fairy from our deck so we can go search for pettingsoeur or Anjelly who are our starters

 

 Awakening of the forest x 1 : I see lots of people using different cards here, mostly Vernusylph of the Thawing or   Vernusylph of the Flourishing hills. i tested each of them and overall i find awakening of the forest better because  in addition of "discarding him and 1 other monster in hand we have, then Spe summon one earth monster from our graveyard" he can make us put one monster from our deck to the graveyard which is very usuful for our deck since Chocolat a la mode or Queen Tiara la fraise need card in our Gy to be activated for exemple. Thawing have the same effect but the additional one is draw 1 which is very good and playable but I find it more usuful to have more gy  material for our xyz than one more card in hand since the deck recycle himself pretty well and we almost never ran out of starter cards. And Vernusylph of the Flourishing hills has for additional effect to tuto one other Vernusylph which is  not that bad but not what we really need in priority in our hand; Beside for non-hand trap version of Madolche i could play it x3 as an addition to our starter engine.

 

 

STAPLE and HANDTRAP:

Katshira Fenrir x3 : it’s a classic, strong and useful in starting hand or when our board is empty.  + it’s an earth monster so he’s also summonable with one of the Vernusylph cards effect.

Our deck can handle monster easily with tiara la fraise so I mostly play handtrap who can counter effect and spell/trap, I don’t find Kaiju necessary in this deck

Ash x 3

Effect Veiler x3

Ghostbelle x1

Harpie feather dust x 1

Infinite perm x3

Mullcharmy Fuwalos x3 : since this cards is new I just added it to the deck. But instead of him if you cannot play him or if it get ban you can totally play 3 nibiru or more draw with 2x upstart goblin and 1 pot of prosperity. Both are playable even if I recommend the 3 nib (we are not afraid of the token thanks to Queen tiarafraise)

 

EXTRA DECK:

 

MADOLCHE CARDS:

 

Teacher Glassouflé x3 : in my opinion our most useful xyz, not scary but easy to place and our only cards who can protect our monster so we need it every time

 

Queen Tiaramasu and Queen Tiarafraise x2 : our most scary cards, no need for 3 because our deck recycling well but 1 is very short if get destroy or banned and you didn’t had time to take it back to the side deck so I go with 2 of them

 

Puddingcess Chocolat-a-la-mode x1 : she’s useful for our first combo but not essential after she did her effect the first time so we can have her only in 1.

Freshsistart x2 : useful to put cards in gy easily and protecting spell, no need for 3 but very useful

Meowcarons x1 : very good for our first combo or in some specific situation but like Chocolat-a-la-mode we very rarely need him more than time in a row

Earth charmer x1 and I:P little night x1 : good links staples, usuful for earth type and in xyz deck during some specific situations

Zeus and Typhon x1 : very good in every xyz deck which is our case

SIDE DECK:

HANDTRAPS:

X3 nibiru, Ghost sister x1 , Dark rullor no more x3 , called by the grave x3 : classical one

MONSTERS:

since madolche is a xyz 4 deck I go with the usual one for a side such as:

 number 41x1  to gain time against attacks

gagaga cowboy x1 to play the time if needed

Traptrix Raflesia and Gravedigger’s traphole cards: for easy negates

 

I then play Undeworld Goddess of the Closed worlds to have an other links for negates, it’s a link 5 but since madolche can spe a lot it can be played in a veey few cased

 

Number 11:  it’s a very powerful and classic xyz 7. If you’re asking yourself why it is here it’s because Katshira fenrir is a lvl 7 monsters, our only one yes, but my luck make me often having two of them on my board so I added number 11 to make them even more useful. It can totally be replaced by something else like Barometh the scacred sheep of Shrubs for exemple.

 

 

 

If anyone is interested I will explain and add a combo list in this deck explanation to play Madolche to it’s fullest potential and i will be very interessed to hear any opinion on the deck.

deck_name: MASTER DUEL - HOW TO PLAY? 1 CARD COMBO WITH NEW SUPPORT MELODIOUS DECK - THE FAIRIES HAVE RETURNED
deck_description: MASTER DUEL Konami have officially announced the new Selection Pack: Geas of the Light! This pack includes new "Melodious" and Illusion support from Legacy of Destruction, as well as the debut of the "Shining Sarcophagus" and modern "Flame Swordsman" deck types! New support for "Madolche" is also here! This pack will update us with new decks and support cards. MASTER DUEL - HOW TO PLAY? 1 CARD COMBO WITH NEW SUPPORT MELODIOUS DECK - THE FAIRIES HAVE RETURNED Below is the deckprofile for everyone's reference.

Have you ever noticed how many Zombies are on the Edison banlist? Turns out, Zombies are extremely good! You can play them as a dedicated strategy, or splash a Zombie engine to enhance another theme or strategy. Both plans are highly effective, running the best Zombies in the format.

 

These monsters are great at keeping more Zombies coming, either replacing themselves or Special Summoning more Zombies. Let's talk about how you can build this deck in different ways, for Edison excellence!
You can run Vaylantz with the Spell Counter Engine which is presently in the main deck or you can take it out and use the Gizmek Engine instead which is in presently in the side deck..

"Ryu-Ge" is a Level 10-focused theme revolving around the Summoning of the three main monsters, as well as the activation of their respective Continuous Spells to grant benefits to the monsters and Summon their boss monster.

Individually, each monster was designed to synergize with the main thematic playing styles associated with the respective Types:

  • "Kuaiba, Rugged Ryu-Ge of Dinocrag" can Special Summon itself from the hand if 2 or more cards were destroyed during the current turn and destroy cards on the field (including the player's own monsters) as an Ignition Effect while the player control it, thus synergizing with Transcendosaurus monsters and generic Dinosaur support cards like "Ground Xeno", "Babycerasaurus", and "Petiteranodon".
  • "Yuanba, Abyssal Ryu-Ge of Serpentfall" can Special Summon itself from the Graveyard if 2 or more monsters were sent from the hand and/or Deck to the GY during the current turn, thus synergizing with Sea Serpent archetypes like "Mermail" and "Atlantean", and its effect to banish the opponent's entire hand fits with hand disruption provided by cards like "Moulinglacia the Elemental Lord" and "Deep Sea Minstrel".
  • "Baba, Champion Ryu-Ge of Wyrmhaze" can Special Summon itself from the banishment if a monster is banished face-up while there are 2 or more banished monsters, thus synergizing with Wyrm archetypes like "Metaphys", "Swordsoul", and "Tenyi", which are focused on banishing their own cards.
  • Finally, although not synergizing with any particular Dragon theme, "Guangba, Luminous Ryu-Ge of Starforge" is amazingly fitting in "Voiceless Voice", an archetype entirely focused on Ritual Summoning LIGHT monsters.

Because of this, each monster can be played separately in pair with the respective Continuous Spell Card as a small yet powerful engine.

deck_excerpt: Generic Crystal Beast list (without staples) to start out with
deck_description:
This is a relatively pure Crystal Beast list before adding non-engine staples. We do run the Spriggan eingine since that just turns any 2 Level 4s into up to 4 monsters instead but otherwise the deck is pretty cookie cutter with some more redundant CB support cards added in to still reach 40 cards but it's a decent start for a competitive Crystal Beast list when you get your hands on some nice staples and want to enter more competitive circles with CBs.

This list is kept stapleless for now so it's relatively cheap and casual to see if you actually like how the deck plays and learn the lines mostly intended for a format that just doesn't run those staples since some people might enjoy that though Crystal Beast (despite the meme status of the deck) has some serious punching power if you manage to summon the 2 Fusion Monsters in succession for a mostly guaranteed 11k punch to your opponent's face so I'm not sure I'd recommend it for such a format...

It had been some time since I made a deck, and i was unsure of what direction to go in. Additionaly, I had always liked the card "Raidraptor - Satellite Cannon Falcon," Due to its unique design and useful effect. When i remebered the card, it inspired me to build a deck focused on the architype. This deck focuses on quickly summoning Raidraptor XYZ monsters, particularly "Raidraptor - Satellite Cannon Falcon", while utilizing Graveyard effects and Rank-Up-Magic cards for powerful plays. The deck's strength lies in its consistency and ability to recover from setbacks. However, it may struggle against decks that can prevent Special Summons or quickly remove XYZ monsters. Once again, I used the Online resorce: https://theresanaiforthat.com/@mmrgaming/yugioh-deck-builder , I cannot stress enough that as an amiture deck builder, it helps alot for figuring out how to get a functional deck from my simplistic ideas. If you end up using this deck, please tell me how I can improve the deck.

deck_excerpt: Has Red-Eyes finally reached it's full potential?
deck_description:
Has Red-Eyes finally reached it's full potential? To quote Red-Eyes Black Dragon's original flavour text, Now it's "a ferocious dragon with a deadly NEGATE!"

What happens when Bystials are relevant in the meta, and a critical mass of handtraps are mandatory to actually play Yugioh? You get this 20+ handtrap monstrosity capable of turboing out Bystial Dis Pater, Chaos Angel and best of all, Red-Eyes Black Fullmetal Dragon!
 
Functioning as a midrange-aggro deck with a robust resource grindgame, Horus Bystial kind of reminds me of Dragonlink except with more Synchro boss monsters and less combo steps! Ever since this interesting strategy's inception and evolution throughout this year, I wanted to give the deck another try after the September 2 TCG banlist because I have a soft spot for unique aggro decks with a "control then OTK" playstyle. 
 
Hardcounter Yubel, Fiendsmith variants, I:P Masquerena and more as you throw a metric ton of Bystials at your opponent while you summon Red-Eyes Black Fullmetal Dragon!

If you want an in-depth guide to this deck, check out my earlier article.

Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

GLHF Duelists!

deck_name: Pendulum Normal Monsters - Underdog Exodia engine
deck_description:
This is not a deck, but a pile of all Pendulum Normal monster cards that are cheap for Master Duel.

You can experiment with them and the "Heart of the underdog" to draw Exodia quite easier.

In the Side deck you can find some expensive SR and UR cards, and some big beatsticks.

Sing, so the Melodious Prayers may Herald the Angels that drive away Tragedy. 

Deckmaster: Diviner of the Herald 
Domain Restriction: LIGHT // FAIRY

Made for Domain Format: https://discord.gg/9Uk2HbpNvN 

Domain Format General Rules:

  • Singleton Format: Every card restricted to 1 copy per deck.
  • 60-card Format: Each Main Deck must contain exactly 60 cards.
  • 4-player Pods: Each player competes individually in an all-out battle against three opponents.
  • Deckmaster Restrictions: Each player chooses a "Deckmaster" which dictates the allowed types and attributes for their deck.
  • Deckmaster Contract: A Deckmaster can be summoned from a designated "Deckmaster Zone" using normal summoning rules. After switching zones, Deckmasters may return to the "Deckmaster Zone," where they start the game.

Refer here for additional rules and exceptions:

https://www.domainformat.com/rules 

Category Breakdown: 

Searchable Removal: Arahime the Manifested Mikanko , Ret-time Reviver Emit-ter , Elder Entity N'tss 
Field Spells: Despia, Theater of the Branded , Trickstar Light Stage , Ritual Sanctuary , Branded Regained 
Life Point Gain: Diana the Light Spirit , Munin the Runick Wings , Cyber Angel Natasha 
Tribute Spells: Enemy Controller , A Major Upset , Mini-Guts , Nibiru, the Primal Being 
Revivals: Fateful Hour , Starry Dragon's Cycle , Branded Banishment , Oasis of Dragon Souls 

What do we want the Deckmaster to do? Diviner of the Herald 
- Removal ( Elder Entity N'tss / Ret-time Reviver Emit-ter)
- Combo Access ( Eva / Trias Hierarchia -> Lo, the Prayers of the Voiceless Voice )
- Field Spell Search ( Valkyrie Sechste -> Valkyrie Funfte -> Rainbow Bridge of Salvation or Despian Tragedy -> Aluber the Jester of Despia -> Despia, Theater of the Branded)
- Ritual Search ( Herald of the Arc Light )

Diviner of Herald has 2 effects, both of which provide advantage by pulling a monster out of deck. Diviner of the Herald is a very important special summon from the deck.
Want to:
Send to GY: Elder Entity N'tss , Ret-time Reviver Emit-ter , Trias Hierarchia , Eva , Despian Tragedy , Herald of the Arc Light 
Special Summon: Valkyrie Sechste , Lo, the Prayers of the Voiceless Voice , Cyber Petit Angel 

What do we want Voiceless Voice to do? 
- Big Beatstick ( Skull Guardian, Protector of the Voiceless Voice )
- Recursive Engine ( Blessing of the Voiceless Voice )

Voiceless Voice is a simple engine that efficiently put a 4100 atk monster that can negate a card. 

What do we want Melodius to do? 
- Easily access boss monster ( Flowering Etoile the Melodious Magnificat )
- Banish cards from GY ( Schuberta the Melodious Maestra )
- Recyle Light Fairies ( Shopina the Melodious Maestra )

Just from 2 fairy monsters, we can access 3 melodious monsters and a way to fuse them together into our choice of Fusion Monster.

What do we want Trickstar to do? 
- Burn

Trickstar does one and one thing only - burn life points. This line, access through Eva adding Trickstar Hoodie and Trickstar Lilybell, will allow us to add two avenues of burn through Trickstar Colchica and Trickstar Noble Angel adding Angel of Blue Tears. 
We can also use Trickstar Band Drummatis to search a s/t removal in Trickstar Light Stage 

 What do we want Runick to do? 
- Protection from removal ( Hugin the Runick Wings ) 
- Life Point Gain ( Munin the Runick Wings )

While Hugin the Runick Wings is traditionally used to add Runick Fountain , in this deck we will use her lesser used second ability to provide protection should we need it. The Runick spells also in of themselves provide wonderful removal effects

Other considerations: 

More Melodius(Aria + Elegy), Purrely , Granguignol the Dusk Dragon , DoSolfachord Coolia , The Weather Painter Rainbow , Dogmatika Ecclesia, the Virtuous , Madolche Anjelly , Mudora the Sword Oracle , Vernusylph of the Misting Seedlings , Kurikara Divincarnate , Archlord Kristya , Couple of Aces 

Enjoy your day.

deck_description: Anime YGO Waking The Dragon, Joey WHEELER deck

1 or 2 card combos with Isolde engine

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. summon "Neo Space Connector" to special summon "Neo-Spacian Aqua Dolphin"

2. Special summon "Isolde, Two Tales of the Noble Knights" and take to hand "Gilford the Lightning"

3. Use Isolde's effect to special summon: "Edea the Heavenly Squire" which will summon "Eidos the Underworld Squire"

4. Normal summon on the same turn "Gilford the Lightning" and destroy all the opponent's monsters.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. summon "Neo Space Connector" to special summon "Neo-Spacian Aqua Dolphin"

2. Special summon "Isolde, Two Tales of the Noble Knights" and take to hand "Gilford the Legend".

3. Use Isolde's effect to special summon: "Armed Samurai - Ben Kei" or "Hayate the earth star" to discard to grave 4-5 equip spells.

4. On your next turn you SHOULD have to your hand and normal summon: "Edea the Heavenly Squire" which will summon "Eidos the Underworld Squire"

5. After that you can normal summon "Gilford the Legend" which can get all 4-5 equip spell cards from grave and use them.

This can be enough to OTK your enemy.

deck_excerpt: "I will beat your a** like a Cherokee Drum"- Dwayne 'The Rock' Johnson
deck_description: Since i have already Made Decks focused on Synchro, XYZ, and Pendulum-Summoning, I wanted to make a fusion Deck. Since the Gem-Kinights have some unique fusion cards, I thought it would be interesting to focus on the Gem-Knights. The deck focuses on quickly summoning powerful Gem-Knight monsters while protecting them and disrupting the opponent. The main strategy revolves around using Gem-Knight Fusion and Brilliant Fusion to bring out key Extra Deck monsters. The Extra Deck provides a toolbox of Fusion monsters for various situations, with Gem-Knight Master Diamond and Lady Brilliant Diamond as the primary powerhouses. The deck can be vulnerable to cards that prevent Special Summoning or negate monster effects. Once again, I used https://theresanaiforthat.com/@mmrgaming/yugioh-deck-builder to help me build the deck. If you have any ideas to help me fix or imprive the deck, please let me know.

deck_excerpt: Dark Strike Fighter FTK ft. Silent Magician Zero
deck_description:
Hey! Watch out for silent dark fighter, who is deadly!

 

 

Gameplan

1) When Shamisen is in your GY and Panda is present, Link Summon Saryuja in a way that only Panda is present. Then, Special Summon "Silent Magician Zero" with Saryuja...

  • You can do the same with Monk as well. Special Summon Monk with Saryuja and if Zero is in your Main Deck, you can use the ability of Monk to pull out Zero from your Main Deck.

2) Place ME-PSY-YA on Pendulum Zone and Special Summon Chaos Emperor Dragon with its ability to unlock "Primal Seed" loop. However, don't banish Shamisen by accident.

3) Give your opponent Zero with "Shien's Spy" and use "Reload" a lot to boost the level of Zero by big margin. When you think it's enough, activate "Enemy Controller" to take Zero back by tributing Saryuja.

4) Use Shamisen in your GY to Special Summon it. Then, you can Synchro Summon "Dark Strike Fighter" with Panda/Monk and Shamisen. Finally, activate Fighter to tribute Zero for the FTK.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contract Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Wonder Wand" and "Spellbook of Knowledge" can be collected by purchasing "Spellbook of Prophecy" deck. 120 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Silent Magician Zero" can be found within "Geas of the Light" Timed Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Into The Void" + "Allure of Darkness" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 180 SR!

- "Moray of Avarice" can be found within "Treasures of the Cosmic Ocean" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Pot of Acquistiveness" + "Ravenous" + "Primal Seed" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 60 SR and 60 UR!

- "Formula Synchron" + "Accel Synchro Stardust Dragon" can be found within "Evoked Dragon of Miracles" Secret Pack to save 90 SR and 30 UR!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 570 SR and 150 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. If you have any questions, feel free to ask. Have fun in Master Duel!

deck_excerpt: Number 43 FTK ft. Silent Magician Zero
deck_description:
Welcome! This deck is another variant of Silent Magician Zero but Number 43 will be used instead to deal the fatal blow.

 

 

Gameplan

1) Link Summon Saryuja in a way that your Main Monster Zones (MMZ) would be empty. Then, place both Pendulum Cards into their Pendulum Zones and Special Summon Chaos Emperor Dragon with its ability to unlock "Primal Seed" loop.

2) Pendulum Summon 3 x DARK monsters. Then, adjust their levels to 2 with "Falling Current", which lets you XYZ Summon Number 43 with these three as materials.

3) Special Summon Zero with Saryuja and gift it to your opponent with "Shien's Spy". Play "Reload" a lot to boost the ATK of Zero. When you think it's enough, activate "Enemy Controller" to take Zero back by tributing Saryuja.

4) Activate "Mystik Wok" and target on Zero. Choose its ATK to gain a huge amount of LP, which can be used for blasting the opponent with Number 43 to win the game.

deck_description: Divine Pendulum Spirit Fusion: Kluger's Redemption is a versatile deck that combines the power of Pendulum Summoning with unique Spirit Pendulum monsters and a potent Fusion engine. At its core, the deck utilizes Pendulum scales to flood the field with monsters, including the recyclable Spirit Pendulums that offer both scale and monster effects. The Fusion component, centered around Elemental HERO Neos Kluger and Neos Fusion, provides access to powerful Extra Deck monsters. This strategy is further supported by a toolbox of Xyz and Link monsters, offering flexible responses to various situations. Key cards like Pendulum Call and Duelist Alliance enhance consistency. âThe deck's strength lies in its ability to swiftly establish strong boards, manage resources effectively, and adapt to matchups.â However, it requires careful piloting to balance its diverse elements and overcome potential vulnerabilities to disruption. With its blend of Pendulum, Spirit, and Fusion mechanics, this deck offers a unique and engaging playstyle that can lead to divine victories on the dueling field. This deck was a lot of fun to make, and it made me remember when I just started to play Yugioh after a long break and got into Pendulum, but now with a lot of power boosts.

deck_description:
A more casual deck, this one focuses on making Ultimate Flame Swordsman (with plenty of way to getting to the starter), it also runs the usual Infernoble suspects and a few extra deck tech options to make it more versatile, at the expense of reliability.

In competitive, you'd probably want to remove Tri-Edge Master and Captain Roland for a second copy of each Charles, and Ferocious Flame Swordsman for a second Isolde.

In the main engine, you could probably trim down to one Field Spell, 2 Fighting Flame Swordsman, Oil to 0, and 1 Fire Flint Lady to make room for more non-engine, and non-engine, as always, is context dependant.

deck_excerpt: Pandor's deck. Trying to bring the best out of her character deck whilst keeping it in the VRAINS era.
deck_description:
Delete Earth, Pandor's deck. Trying to bring the best out of her character deck whilst keeping it in the VRAINS era. I'm not that knowledgeable on VRAINS so my apologies if anything seems off.

Let me know if you've got any ideas to improve it.

The deck feels much better to play by replacing 6 searchers (Tachyon & Ascension) that are basically a -1 in a handtrap heavy deck (You even have to discard for Tydel). Instead, Azamina engine is small and provide another method of putting bodies on board before going into your ryzeal line and Argos line.

1) Keep in mind of these restrictions:
Thode Ryzeal: Locks you into rank 4 when he is special summoned
Ex Ryzeal: Locks you into rank 4 when he is special summoned AND his search effect can only be activated when you control only rank 4 and/or level 4 monster on the field. So make sure to go into azamina line first before before ryzeal line if you can.

2) Keep in mind the interaction of azamina cards:
Summon Rcielago search WANTED -> use WANTED to search for Diabellestar -> Diabellestar sends Rcielago to GY to summon herself and set another Deception -> return Sacred Azamina to hand by putting back Rcielago from GY into extra deck -> summon out either azamina extra deck monster by sending the 2nd deception
You can also activate Sacred Azamina and chain WANTED, Sacred Azamina will resolve by sending face up WANTED to the GY

3) Regarding Azalea in the extra deck
Azalea is a great card as she remove 1 card on opponent side of the field while also removing herself from outside of the field to make way for Ryzeal engine

4) Regarding shifter in the side deck
Azamina engine will not work under shifter so when siding in shifter, azamina engine is among the top priority to be sided out

deck_excerpt: (no staples) The Favorite Hero will make his fist contact your face
deck_description:
A very non-competitive Neos deck capable of kind of consistently Cosmo Locking the opponent and otherwise doing some HERO shenanigans.

I put in one level 4 E Hero of each attribute for lore reasons and because most of them are really good (Prisma admittedly is a bit too slow for the deck but we'll manage) so this is an actual E-Hero and Neo Spacian mish mash deck that genuinely works (making it a modern S2-4 Jaden deck)

As for the abseences of Air Hummingbird and Glow Moss: The Neos that shall not be named is too expensive to consider while the Glow Neos lines are just terrible... Storm Neos and Chaos Neos are pretty niche and very win more since if you manage to summon them their payoff won't be worth it anymore or the can seriously screw you over in the case of Chaos Neos (even though it looks awesome AF) so we're left with Nebula Neos and Magma Neos for the Triple Contacts who don't suck major balls compared to the other 2.

Aqua Neos and Marine Dolphin are some fun little additions to keep Neos Fusion and Instant Contact live while also being able to rip cards out of the opponent's hand.

Elemental HERO Core is just in here because he's my favourite HERO monster opposed to Jaden's fixation on Neos and he can float into a dead Shining Neos Wingman to lay down even more devastation, Absolute Zero to put some more pressure on the opponent to play around the board wipe, Infernal Rage to search/recycle for another Favorite Contact or any 1-Spacian Neos Fusion that might've died before which can then recycle itself into the Extra Deck.

Main Playmaker is of course A Hero Lives to get a combo started but there's some other less ideal lines we can also attempt to play through.

From just A Hero Lives we can grab Stratos who will in turn get Blazeman.

NS Blazeman to search Poly and use Blazeman and Stratos as material for Infernal Devicer.

Devicer searches Neos and a Neo Spacian (Maybe Aqua Dolphin or whatever you're missing in your opening hand for a Triple or Cosmo Neos).

Poly Devicer + Neos into Sunrise who will search Miracle Fusion.

Miracle Fuse Blazeman and Stratos/Neos into Flame Wingman - Infernal Rage who will search for Favorite Contact.

Set Favorite Contact which can summon a Hero Fusion Monster during your opponent's turn (probably Shining Neos Wingman).

As long as you can use Neos for what you want to summon I'd recommend banishing him for the Miracle Fusion since Favorite Contact also uses banished cards and puts them back into the deck. Of course if your hand has more things other than A Hero Lives your plays can be way more varied to include some more interesting HEROs like Solid/Liquid Soldier, Absolute Zero, Dark Law etc.

A really fun play of the deck is to use Liquid Soldier as a Fusion Material while having Cross Keeper in grave to essentially mulligan your hand by drawing 2 twice and putting one of them into the grave and one under the deck.

Since this is a Neos deck I didn't want to bother with staples because let's be honest: No way in hell this will ever be competitive but it's a fun list to learn/illustrate combo lines and different intricacies of the Fusion mechanic since we have regular Fusion from the hand/field (Poly), Tagging Out (Mask Change), Fusion from the grave (Miracle Fusion), Contact Fusing, Instant Fusing (Instant Contact), absolute Bullshit (Favorite Contact) and not Fusing at all but still summoning the appropriate monster (Neos Fusion) as well as Summoning Condition Ignorance (Now that I look at that list of features I get why people say this is a game for lawyers xD)

deck_excerpt: Deceitful Dice FTK ft. Treasure Panda
deck_description:
Greetings! In today's deck, we are on a roll to burn down the opponent with a deceitful dice!

 

 

Gameplan

1) Place ME-PSY-YA on Pendulum Zone and Special Summon Chaos Emperor Dragon with its ability to unlock "Primal Seed" loop.

2) Whether you have discarded Deceitful and Gaap to GY with Dugares/Ravenous or you keep one of them in hand, use Saryuja and "Monster Reborn" to place both on the battlefield.

3) If you want to kill the opponent, Deceitful has to be activated as Chain Link 3. "Primal >>> Moon >>> Deceitful" combination should do the trick. Repeat until you win the game.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Monster Reborn" can be found by completing the tutorial to save 30 UR!

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contract Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Wonder Wand" and "Spellbook of Knowledge" can be collected by purchasing "Spellbook of Prophecy" deck. 120 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Number 60: Dugares the Timeless" can be found within "Number Recall" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Into The Void" + "Allure of Darkness" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 180 SR!

- "Moray of Avarice" can be found within "Treasures of the Cosmic Ocean" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Pot of Acquistiveness" + "Ravenous" + "Gaap the Divine Soldier" + "Primal Seed" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 90 SR and 60 UR!

- "Formula Synchron" + "Accel Synchro Stardust Dragon" can be found within "Evoked Dragon of Miracles" Secret Pack to save 60 SR and 30 UR!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 570 SR and 180 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. If you have any questions, feel free to ask. Have fun in Master Duel!

deck_excerpt: ygoprodeck.com, yugipedia.com, yugioh.fandom.com, yugiohtopdecks.com, ygorganization.com, rushcard.io, discordapp.com/discord.gg, imgur.com
deck_description:
1. Pendulum Summoning

Overview: Pendulum Summoning is a unique method that allows you to summon multiple monsters simultaneously from your hand or face-up from the Extra Deck.

How It Works:

Pendulum Zones: Place two Pendulum Monsters in the leftmost and rightmost Spell & Trap Card Zones. These zones become Pendulum Zones.

Pendulum Scale: Each Pendulum Monster has a scale value. As long as the scales are set, you can Pendulum Summon monsters whose levels fall between the scales.

Summoning: Simply announce your Pendulum Summon and place eligible monsters on the field from your hand or face-up Extra Deck.

Key Cards: Use cards like "Performapal Monkeyboard" and "Performapal Celestial Magician" to set the scales and facilitate summoning.

 

2. Fusion Summoning

Overview: Fusion Summoning combines two or more monsters into a single, powerful Fusion Monster using a Fusion Spell Card.

How It Works:

Requirements: Gather Fusion Material monsters specified on the Fusion Monster card.

Fusion Spell: Activate a card like "Neos Fusion" or "Fusion Destiny" to initiate the Fusion Summon.

Summoning: Send the materials to the Graveyard or as specified, then summon the Fusion Monster from your Extra Deck.

Key Cards: Utilize "Elemental HERO Neos Kluger" and "Destiny HERO - Destroyer Phoenix Enforcer".

 

3. Xyz Summoning

Overview: Xyz Summoning involves overlaying monsters of the same level to summon an Xyz Monster, which ranks at the level of those monsters.

How It Works:

Materials: Use two or more monsters of the same level as Xyz Materials.

Overlay: Place the Xyz Materials under the Xyz Monster card vertically.

Summoning: Declare the Xyz Summon and place the Xyz Monster in the Monster Zone.

Key Cards: "Number 61: Volcasaurus" is a prime target for Xyz Summoning.

 

4. Synchro Summoning

Overview: By combining a Tuner monster and one or more non-Tuner monsters, you can Synchro Summon powerful Synchro Monsters.

How It Works:

Requirements: Use one Tuner and one or more non-Tuner monsters whose total levels equal the Synchro Monster's level.

Summoning: Declare the Synchro Summon, then send the materials to the Graveyard and bring out the Synchro Monster.

Key Cards: Use "Enlightenment Paladin" for Synchro Summoning.

 

5. Ritual Summoning

Overview: Ritual Summoning calls upon a powerful Ritual Monster, usually requiring a specific Ritual Spell and tribute of monsters.

How It Works:

Ritual Spell: Have a Ritual Spell Card and the corresponding Ritual Monster in your hand.

Tributes: Sacrifice monsters from your field or hand equal to the Ritual Monster's level.

Summoning: Activate the Ritual Spell and summon the Ritual Monster to your field.

Key Cards: "Preparation of Rites" can help retrieve important Ritual Spell Cards and monsters.

 

6. Link Summoning

Overview: Link Summoning allows you to bring out a Link Monster using any number of monsters as specified, ignoring levels and ranks.

How It Works:

Materials: Check the Link Monster's instructions for required materials.

Zones: Make sure you have a Main Monster Zone or Extra Monster Zone pointed to by Link Arrows.

Link Markers: Consider Link Arrows when planning future plays and placements.

Summoning: Use the specified number of monsters, sending them to the Graveyard, and place the Link Monster in the zone.

Key Cards: Utilize "I:P Masquerena" and "Beyond the Pendulum" for strategic Link Summons.

deck_excerpt: Blue Eyes Occhi Blu Domain Format UmbaTCG
deck_description:
ITALIANO

Ciao! La Deck Master e' la vecchia Maiden per X motivi che ho spiegato nella clip, il mazzo vuole provare di giocare veramente come un mazzo Occhi Blu e non risultare una pila informe di Engine generici (che però volendo e' fattibilissima essendo poi imbullonato il mazzo sui luce). Anche cosi' ha un buon power level e riesce a difendersi dai mazzi forti del Formato. In Side ho lasciato alcuni spunti ed idee per modificare qualche rateo, altre opzioni meno ovvie potrebbero essere gli Hieratic o provare di pivottare un po' di piu' sui gialloni. 

ENGLISH

Hi! The Deck Master is the old and super iconic Maiden for various reasons that I explained in the clip. The deck aims to truly play like a Blue-Eyes deck rather than just being a random pile of generic engines (though that's certainly possible if desired, being light-based you can do pretty cool stuff). Even so, it has a good power level and can hold its own against the stronger decks in the Format. In the Side, I've included some ideas and suggestions for adjusting a few ratios; other less obvious options could be adding Hieratics (+Bystials) or leaning a bit more into the Dragon Vanillas.

deck_excerpt: Hello, I am just getting back into yugioh. Here is a deck I thought might work but I'm open to feedback for improvement.
deck_description:
I basically remember Heros and dark whole and build from there. I learned about ZERO, dark law and Dark Hole Dragon and thought there might be a way to make that work as a sort of dead man's switch. This is a first draft so I am welcome for advice.

 

The basic engine is a basic dark law heros deck. You have your Stratos combo to get DL on the field but I added more heros and chances to get ZERO out as well. 

The the DL deck itself is an effective deck but what you want is to get DHD in your hand or grave and then either DH the board to get him out, have the opponents take a monster out to activate his effect OR get ZERO on the board. Zero if killed will wipe the board activating DHDs effect and you now have a free 3000 atk monster. If you have DL on the field as well all their monster are banished. It theoretical works by making your opponent have no good options for killing anything. You run ash and some of the extra deck to adapt if need be. 

 

This really is new to me and I am having people look at this as well. I have been told DHD does better with other cards but I like Heros and if I can get DHD to even function like I want in it I think it is a win. This is also the first deck I have posted and have no idea how any of this works so please understand I am learning. Thank you and maybe this can give you some inspirational to build something goofy like this in the future.

deck_description: This list is by no means competitive. It's just something I have to play against a friend casually.

Untested, but theoretically good. All the Ryu-Ge monsters have effects in hand to remove themselves from your hand to add their respective continuous spells to hand from deck. the only one that doesnt benefit from this hand removal is Kuaiba, shuffling itself back into the deck when it wants to stay in your hand. The others meanwhile pitch and banish themselves, Baba even bringing to hand its own summoning condition with its spell that becomes a Dimmension Fissure on your opponent's turn. When 2 or more monsters are sent to the grave from hand or deck, or banished, you can special Yuanba and Baba respectively. Yubel loves to destroy, and can even destroy itself from the deck. This kind of effect fulfills the requirments of 3 cards to summon themselves; Kuaiba, Yuanba, and Guangba, being able to summon from hand with destructions, from grave with dumps, and from face-up extra deck with destructions. When Guangba is on the field with all three continuous spells, it gains three once per turn quick effects in a negate, a bounce, and an attack debuff. That in tandem with the combo potential of Yubel bringing out Phantom's effect change, High King Wave Caesar's special negate, and Desirae's omni negate makes for a brutal potential end board.

I tried to give another chance for Morphtronics.
They have a huge potential, and I hope this deck can show this

deck_excerpt: Quarter Century Bonanza has reprinted the last expensive Ancient Gear cards!
deck_description:
Quarter Century Bonanza has reprinted the last expensive Ancient Gear cards like Ancient Gear Fortress and Ancient Gear Ballista - so now this OTK fan-favourite is now extremely accessible!

My FAVOURITE archetype of ALL TIME has been occassionally topping tournaments despite not being at full power (Ancient Gear Statue isn't out yet), so I thought I would try it out vs. the November 2024 TCG meta! Welcome to my master class in PhD in dueling aspiring Ancient Gear soldier!

Ancient Gear Dark Golem, Ancient Gear Statue, Ancient Gear Advance, Ancient Gear Commander, Ancient Gear Tanker and Ancient Gear Duel all make it much easier to generate an entire army of Ancient Gear killer robots to obliterate all your opponent's board and lifepoints with! Now there is a heavy emphasis on Dr. Crowler's ace monster, Ancient Gear Golem, and now we're actually incentivized to summon it a lot and make fusion boss monsters like Ultimate Ancient Gear Golem and Megaton Golem! 

Let's blind second and teach these our SLIFER SLACKERS opponents what the true meaning of what it means to have a PhD in dueling, just like our beloved Dr. Vellian Crowler! Time to blind second, and MECHANIZED MELEE all opposition that we come across!

If you want a thorough guide on hwo to play this deck, click on this link.

deck_description:
This is a combination of 3 archetypes. Nordics , Aesir and Relics cards. Aesir cards are the Synchro Gods Odin, Thor and Loki. Relics are trap cards that act as equip cards but only for 1 turn. Nordics is the basic archetype of all small monsters.

Let's start with some basics, we want to summon the Aesir Gods but every card has different rules which specifies the name of the tuner card + that it needs at least 3 monsters as synchro materials (1 tuner and 2 or more non-tuner). We can cheat out the first limitation by using "Vanadis of the Nordic Ascendant" as a substitute or we can even use the effect of "Alviss of the Nordic Alfar" combined with "Gullveig of the Nordic Ascendant" to skip the tuner card too.

While most players are using something like 30 Nordic monsters so they can normal summon 1 Nordic, to special summon "Gullveig of the Nordic Ascendant" and then banish 3 more cards (and practically lose 4 cards) to summon a God. It is more efficient to summon a God with only 2 cards.

First you normal summon a Nordic monster then you special summon "Gullveig of the Nordic Ascendant" and banish from hand "Alviss of the Nordic Alfar". After that you can even skip the tuner monster and use as materials whatever you want (with the cost of 2 cards instead of 4). One useful tip I can give you is that it's better with "Alviss of the Nordic Alfar" effect to discard from deck the most useless Nordic monsters (most of the times the level 4 and some level 3 beast-type cards).

While reading the effects of the Gods you might think that they are very strong and with the protection of "Gullveig of the Nordic Ascendant" even more invicible, but this is not true. While it's easy to summon the first God, it's way more difficult to summon the second and you have to play for multiple turns with only 1 attacking monster which is quite slow. What is problematic with Aesir Gods is that their effects are once per turn and only in your turn. Mostly you will find the Odin as the best one, while the others are so more useless (that's why my Extra deck is not full of them).

To reach the level 10 of synchro materials you basically need:

4+4+2 or 4+3+3 which as a result shows us that we need more level 4 monsters than level 3 or 2.

Now by watching at the deck you can find x5 level 2, x5 level 3 and x10 level 4 monsters which is the sweet spot for me. To make a God with the efficient combo you lose around 5 Nordic monsters from your main deck.

Most decks you can find on youtube are a pile of 30 nordic monsters without some short of protection or alternative ways of playing via XYZ cards for example. One big minus of these decks is that they use tuner cards but they don't have other Synchro monsters aside of the Aesir Gods. Just to remind you that Aesir Gods need a lot of materials and sometimes specified materials to get summoned, while generic Synchro cards do not. So, cards like "Black Rose Dragon", "Stardust Dragon" (which can be used as a protector) and "Draco Berserker of the Tenyi" can be used to extend the plays.

But what's the weaknesses of this deck?

1. It's possible that your opponent can negate the effect of "Gullveig of the Nordic Ascendant" (by "Effect Veilor) or even destroy it. That's why cards as "Destruction Jammer" and "Forbidden dress" are godsend ("Forbidden Dress doesn't need a setup).

2. There is not enough protection from cards like "Raigeki" that doesn't target the Aesir Gods. So you might need something even more drastically than one-turn-protection cards. What comes to mind are: "Power of the Guardians" and "Dimension Guardian". I think that I prefer "Dimension Guardian" as a surprise (jumpscare) card, while "Power of the Guardians" is way more searchable.

3. As I said before the game pacing is quite slow and most of the times the only attacking monster is going to be "Odin". So your enemy is going to play the defensive role till he draw his "Raigeki" or "Dark Hole". So my idea was to add some piercing dmg, cause cards like "Divine Relic Mjollnir" and "Nordic Relic Megingjord" can possibly make an one-turn-kill. To do so we have "Fairy Meteor Crush", "Big Bang Shot" and "H - Heated Heart".

a) "Big Bang Shot" gives our monster a very big disadvantage <<When this spell card leaves the field, banish the equipped monster>>.

b) "Fairy Meteor Crush" on the other hand is an equipped card as "Big Bang Shot", which means that before "Odin" attacks, to protect himself from trap cards like "Mirror force" we should active it's effect. By activating it, all the spell cards effects on "Odin" are negated...

c) "H - Heated Heart" on the other hand is an one-turn-card, but it can't be negated if it's activated firstly on "Odin" and then "Odin" activates his own effect.

I don't want to overdo it with even more details and more in-depth combos. I am quite disappointed with Nordic cards. After the Link card's support, it doesn't matter most of the Nordic monster's effects, cause they've being used just as materials ( we don't even care for tuner cards, at a Synchro-Based deck... LOL). That's a shame and I was about to give up on this deck, but then I've found so bad deck profiles on the internet (as always) so... here we are today.

This is a pure build for fun matches until you hit Diamond.
(I am counting Destrudo + Garura as Zombies, one is mandatory the other counts because of his badass artwork.)

I have included other niche cards who are paying life point in the Side-Deck.


Introduction:
Sadly, our available cards to play a pure Zombie-Deck with cool artworks are limited.
The future doesn’t look much brighter.

Even with cards like The Duke of Demise, Flying Mary, the Wandering Ghost Ship, Wandering Titan of Tartarus or the new announced +Delta of Temptation the main weakness of the deck remains. We cannot play through handtraps.
You need at least 2 specific cards to set up Zombie World+Balerdroch. One normal summon of Gozuki is not enough.

I’m not a fan of archetypes. I like the deckbuilding aspect of Zombie-Deck.
But we lack the ability to search for cards and to add them to one’s hand. A special summon of the hand with an additional graveyard or search effect might work wonders. For comparison we don’t have a way to search for a spell or trap like Mathmechs do with Mathmech Superfactorial.

Furthermore, we don’t have enough space for handtraps or board breakers ourselves.


Cool interactions:

1)You can use the banish effect from Balerdroch as an extension to your plays by banishing Alghoul Mazera or Changshi.

2) Effect Gozuki to send Changshi → summon an extra deck monster with Gozuki and an additional monster → effect Gozuki to special one Zombie from hand by banishing Changshi → effect Changshi to banish Gozuki from GY to special → profit.

This is also why I am not a fan of Uni-Zombie. One Effect Veiler of Imperm ends your plays.

3) By playing the Vendread package you get access to another level 6 Monster. Also, you can activate the first effect “Vendread Savior”.


GL & HF
Zombieman

deck_excerpt: Nurse Burn FTK ft. Cosmic Tree
deck_description:
Hi there! Recently, "Cosmic Tree Irmistil" has been released on Master Duel and I decided to try with Nurse deck. If you like Nurse decks, you can check this one to see different variations one may come up with.

 

 

Gameplan

1) Place ME-PSY-YA on Pendulum Zone and Special Summon "Black Luster Soldier" (BLS) with its ability to unlock "Primal Seed" loop. Then, Special Summon Nurse with Saryuja.

2) Fill your side of the board with Effect Monsters via "Monster Reborn". Then, Link Summon Cosmic Tree with all but BLS and give Cosmic Tree to your opponent with "Shien's Spy".

3) To burn your opponent with Nurse, all you need to do is revive monsters with "Monster Reborn". You can start with Nurse and follow up with monsters from highest ATK to lowest ones. It doesn't have to be original ATK, which means that modifications coming from cards like Ravenous should do the trick and end the game on the spot...

  • Although not shown in this game, there is a loop. You can revive Saryuja and banish it with BLS. Then, return Saryuja to Extra Deck with "Primal Seed" and Link Summon Saryuja with 4 monsters, one of which has to be BLS and shouldn't be Nurse. Next, revive BLS to enable "Primal Seed" loop and reset BLS, so that you can banish Saryuja and repeat this process.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Monster Reborn" can be found by completing the tutorial to save 30 UR!

- "Black Luster Soldier - Envoy of the Beginning" can be collected by purchasing "Spiral Spear Strike" deck. 30 UR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contract Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Cosmic Tree Irmistil" can be found within "Geas of the Light" Timed Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Number 60: Dugares the Timeless" can be found within "Number Recall" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Into The Void" + "Allure of Darkness" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 180 SR!

- "Moray of Avarice" can be found within "Treasures of the Cosmic Ocean" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Pot of Acquistiveness" + "Ravenous" + "Primal Seed" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 60 SR and 60 UR!

- "Formula Synchron" + "Accel Synchro Stardust Dragon" can be found within "Evoked Dragon of Miracles" Secret Pack to save 60 SR and 30 UR!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 570 SR and 210 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.
